A woman was shot and wounded in Friday night's attack. CAPE TOWN - Police are investigating an attempted murder following a shooting at a filling station in Delft. A woman was shot and wounded in Friday night's attack. A video of the incident has been doing the rounds on social media. It shows a gunman approaching a vehicle at a filling station. The gunman fires directly at the person in the front passenger seat before the driver speeds off. The police's Noloyiso Rwexana: "No one has been arrested at this stage. The detectives are following up on all possible leads to bring the perpetrators to book. We appeal to the public to come forward with any information to assist us with our investigation. They are requested to contact Crime Stop on 08600 10111."